{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/html/intro-to-css-and-separation-of-concerns/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Previously we wrote styles directly on HTML elements. That is not the most convenient way, because imagine managing 50 files like those and what amount of effort it would take to just change the font style across all of them.</p>\n<p>This is where the term \"Separation of Concerns\" comes in. It means that each file should be responsible for it's own thing. HTML files are meant to hold content, not styles. We have a different language to write the styles of a web page in. It's called CSS.</p>\n<p>CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. Style sheets mean that the file contains only CSS code. Cascading means that it is read top to bottom and anything above can be changed by a new style below.</p>\n<p>Let's start fresh with only the html, head and body tags in your index.html file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>head</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>head</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  \n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>To create a stylesheet, create a new file right next to your \"index.html\", name it \"styles.css\" (for stylesheet) and then link it to the HTML document with a <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;link&gt;</code> tag, like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>head</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>link</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">rel</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>stylesheet<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>/styles.css<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>head</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  \n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now create a heading element with some text in it.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>head</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>link</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">rel</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>stylesheet<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>/styles.css<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>head</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet.<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now open your \"styles.css\" and write:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">h1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> red<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>You should now see your text turn red!</p>\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"300\" src=\"//jsfiddle.net/itshazy/qotpmg9k/embedded/html,css,result/dark/\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" allowpaymentrequest frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\n<p>The CSS is very basic, you're targeting the \"h1\" element directly and changing the value, of the property called \"color\" to \"red\".\nYou can add any color you want. Even in Hex and RGB color codes.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">h1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> #FF0000<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">h1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">rgb</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>255<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>0<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>0<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Both of the above will still color the text red. This is the proper way of styling HTML elements and their content. You can target elements in a few more ways and one way is more \"powerful\" than the previous. The way we targeted is by <strong>targeting the element</strong>. You can also target by <strong>class</strong>.</p>\n<h1>Targeting By Class</h1>\n<p>Clear everything out of the \"styles.css\" file except this code:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">h1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> red<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now add a \"class selector\" like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">h1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> red<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token selector\">.my-class</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> green<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>And now make the CSS selector actually find the target in the linked HTML file by adding a \"class\" property to an HTML element, like this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>head</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>link</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">rel</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>stylesheet<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">href</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>/styles.css<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>head</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>my-class<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet.<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>body</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>html</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>And surely enough, the heading turned green!</p>\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"300\" src=\"//jsfiddle.net/itshazy/4j1ep8us/1/embedded/html,css,result/dark/\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" allowpaymentrequest frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\n<h1>Separation of Concern</h1>\n<p>I wish to highlight this idea again, because it's ultimately important to be lazy in programming. If you have to do the same exact thing 3 or more times in a row, over and over again, you could probably automate it. </p>\n<p>In the context of HTML and CSS, separation of concerns allows you to now link this CSS file in as many HTML files you want and unless there are styles in the HTML itself, that say otherwise, all of the \"h1\" headings should turn green. This minimizes the places you need to add changes down to one. The CSS file.</p>\n<p>When creating programs, always try and imagine how code should be separated by it's main concern. </p>\n<p>The content lives in HTML files. </p>\n<p>The styles live in CSS files.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Intro to CSS and Separation of Concerns","index":3}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"excerpt":"HTML or Hyper Text Markup Language serves as the backbone that holds all of the content of any webpage. Literally all of them. \"Even giants…","fields":{"slug":"/html/what-is-html/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-02-23T00:00:00.000Z","title":"What is HTML?","categories":["HTML"],"index":0},"timeToRead":3}},{"node":{"excerpt":"Since HTML is used to structure entire web pages, then let's write one! Open the same index.html file we used in the previous post and…","fields":{"slug":"/html/html-pages/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-02-23T00:00:00.000Z","title":"HTML Pages","categories":["HTML"],"index":1},"timeToRead":3}},{"node":{"excerpt":"In the previous post we looked at the different elements that are most commonly used in websites. Let’s talk about layout. Obviously, after…","fields":{"slug":"/html/html-layout-and-styles/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-02-23T00:00:00.000Z","title":"HTML Layout and Styles","categories":["HTML"],"index":2},"timeToRead":11}},{"node":{"excerpt":"Previously we wrote styles directly on HTML elements. That is not the most convenient way, because imagine managing 50 files like those and…","fields":{"slug":"/html/intro-to-css-and-separation-of-concerns/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-02-24T00:00:00.000Z","title":"Intro to CSS and Separation of Concerns","categories":["HTML"],"index":3},"timeToRead":3}}]}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/html/intro-to-css-and-separation-of-concerns/","category":"HTML","index":3}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}